{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/560/comments/117264477.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/560/_/diff#comment-117264477"}}, "parent": {"id": 117263664, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/560/comments/117263664.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/560/_/diff#comment-117263664"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 560, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/560.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/560"}}, "title": "WIP: Frame semantics for sdf 1.7"}, "content": {"raw": "One solution to make \\(a\\) feasible is to add `//joint/axis[@relative_to]` \\(or perhaps more accurately, `@expressed_in`?\\), and then transformation is simply replacing `use_parent_model_frame` with `relative_to=\u201d<model>\u201d`, and the joint pose can still be whatevs. Granted, that may make things a bit noisy.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>One solution to make (a) feasible is to add <code>//joint/axis[@relative_to]</code> (or perhaps more accurately, <code>@expressed_in</code>?), and then transformation is simply replacing <code>use_parent_model_frame</code> with <code>relative_to=\u201d&lt;model&gt;\u201d</code>, and the joint pose can still be whatevs. Granted, that may make things a bit noisy.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-17T19:29:05.846822+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Eric Cousineau", "uuid": "{71c9fc05-02c8-45e1-adfa-13c8ac3399dc}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B71c9fc05-02c8-45e1-adfa-13c8ac3399dc%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B71c9fc05-02c8-45e1-adfa-13c8ac3399dc%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557057:f3a199b9-5784-4964-9644-6ef224bc7dc1/28a4d748-0fd4-4038-bf3d-55a77eb73ede/128"}}, "nickname": "eacousineau", "type": "user", "account_id